description:
&lt;p&gt;Frimley Park Critical Care is looking to appoint a Band 5 staff nurse to join our Critical Care Team. We are seeking to appoint a motivated and dynamic Registered Nurse who wishes to pursue a structured Band 5 critical care development programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Frimley Park Critical Care Unit has 12 beds consisting of a mixture of ITU/HDU patients (Level 3 and Level 2). Our education programmes, supported by our practice education team, aim to provide staff of all grades with the essential knowledge and skills required to work on our busy, friendly unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a minimum of 6 months relevant post registration experience in an acute hospital setting, and up-to-date knowledge, together with a willingness to develop acute care skills and the ability to integrate into our dynamic team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a flexible work pattern by offering both short and long shifts, all staff will be expected to rotate onto night duty. Opportunities are available to advance through AFC gateways through frameworks of development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rita Mody, Senior Sister ICU or Mary Virtue, Clinical Matron, ICU&lt;/p&gt;
